# Packages list in LOG.MD

When adding, removing, or replacing a direct dependency, update the **Packages** section in `LOG.MD`.

## What to list
- Direct deps only (not transitive): `backend/pyproject.toml`, `frontend/package.json`, `engine/Cargo.toml`, and other first-party manifests.
- Prefer the upstream **GitHub repo** URL (or the project's primary source repo) so packages can be starred.
- Group by layer: Backend, Frontend, Engine (Rust), Infra/tooling.
- Skip private/internal packages and pure tooling with no public repo only if there truly is none.

## Format

```markdown
## Packages

### Backend
- [fastapi](https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi) — API framework

### Engine (Rust)
- [tokio](https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio) — async runtime
```

## When
- Same change set as the dependency edit (or the next LOG entry for that work).
- Also append a normal dated Log line for the meaningful progress.
